Interface JavaContainer<E>

Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements in the container
All Known Implementing Classes:
JavaSet, JavaVector
public interface JavaContainer<E>
The JavaContainer interface is a generic container that can hold elements of type E. It defines methods for adding and removing elements, retrieving the size of the container, obtaining an iterator over its elements, and writing its contents to a file.
